I really like the approach of allowing either kind of call, with the &quot;dot&quot; style mere convenience over the function style. Rust has that sort of thing:<p><pre><code>    let v = &vec![1u32,2,3];
    println!(&quot;{}&quot;, v.len());
    println!(&quot;{}&quot;, Vec::len(v));</code></pre>
